The paper deals with the impact of communication delays on distributed consensus algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves the modeling and analysis of communication delays, which can be seen as a Systems and Control (cs.SY) problem. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of consensus protocols, which is a topic in Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also involves the analysis of convergence rates, which can be seen as an Information Theory (cs.IT) problem. Finally, the paper proposes the use of a different consensus algorithm, which can be seen as a topic in Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA).
